<h2>What Stacc Is Seeing Across 3,500 Blogs</h2>
<p>A note from our own production data, because the headline numbers above are aggregated. Across the blogs we published in Q1 2026:</p>
<p>The pieces that pulled the most traffic relative to length were not the longest. They were the ones with a single named framework, two original data points, and clean structural blocks. The pieces that earned the most AI citations had three things in common: clear definitions in the first 200 words, named statistics that read as quotable, and a perspective the rest of the SERP did not have.</p>
<p>The pieces that underperformed were the ones that tried to be everything to everyone. "Ultimate guide" without a point of view. We have stopped writing those. They were never that good, and they are now actively penalized by both Google and the AI engines that scrape them.</p>
